              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/taf/tafp5#TrainState</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Characterizes the state of the Train (as a physical asset), e.g. speed, mass, GPS coordinates of some particular point of the train, etc.
Since the subclasses are not disjoint, the ontology user is free to use a single individual to combine information. Ultimately, most useful combinations should give rise to dedicated subclasses, in the interest of efficient data serialization and transformation to/from document formats such as JSON or XML.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
